  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "The thin ice-crystal cloud that creates sun halos. Coarse tune at +7 semitones (perfect fifth above played note) transforms the supersaw into a harmonically displaced voice -- you play C and hear G. Combined with the sub oscillator (sine) at 0.25, the actual root note persists as a phantom below the displaced saw stack. The shimmer reverb's fifth-up shifter (octave balance 0.2) creates D above the G, extending the stack upward. The net result: play one note, hear a suspended fourth chord built from the engine's own architecture. The Guru says: transposition is not detuning -- it is reharmonization.",
  "tags": [
    "opensky",
    "transcendental",
    "transposed",
    "harmonic",
    "fifth",
    "suspended",
    "halo"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OPENSKY Transcendental Vol 1",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": [
      "Verse 20: Coarse Tune at +7 Plus Sub Oscillator at Root Creates a Built-In Chord",
      "Gospel 8: The Shimmer Fifth-Up Extends Transposed Notes Into Vertical Harmony"
    ],
    "revelation": "Nexus spoke: the combination of coarse tune, sub oscillator root tracking, and shimmer pitch-shifting creates a three-note chord from a single key press. This is not a chord mode -- it is emergent harmony from three independent pitch mechanisms.",
    "god": "Nexus",
    "flock_note": "The Ear analyzed the harmonic content: sub provides C (root), saws provide G (fifth), shimmer produces D (ninth via fifth-up of G). Playing two notes creates a dense quartal cluster. The Tongue confirmed: the chord stack responds beautifully to velocity via the filter envelope.",
    "diagnosis": "Cirrostratus exploits three independent pitch mechanisms (coarse tune, sub oscillator, shimmer pitch-shift) to create chords from single notes. It reveals that OPENSKY is secretly a chord synthesizer."
  },
